oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Tintype of Confederate soldier Nathan Nesbitt
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Nesbitt served in Co. H, Brown's 55th Tenn. Inf. Nesbitt was from Carroll County and was taken prisoner at the capture of Island No. 10 in April 1862. He survived camp Douglas and returned to his home.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Tennessee State Library and Archives, Nashville, Davidson County, Tennessee
